 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Time-resolved luminescence measurements</div>
 <p id="Par10" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Time-resolved luminescence measurements were performed by using FluoroMax 4 (Horiba) in a time-correlated single-photon counting (TCSPC) mode. For excitation, a LED source (Horiba) with the excitation wavelength set to λ
  <sub>ex</sub> = 371 nm and the repetition rate set to 1 MHz was used. The resulting luminescence signal was detected at an emission wavelength of λ
  <sub>em</sub> = 655 nm. The luminescence decay curves were fitted multiexponentially with 
  <span class="italic">α</span>
  <sub>i</sub> being the amplitude of the 
  <span class="italic">i</span>th component with the corresponding decay time 
  <span class="italic">τ</span>
  <sub>i</sub> (Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ1" ref-type="" href="#Equ1">1</a>)). Additionally, the intensity-weighted average decay time 
  <span class="italic">τ</span>
  <sub>av(int)</sub>, which is calculated according to Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ2" ref-type="" href="#Equ2">2</a>), was used. The goodness of the fits was judged on the reduced 
